title.narrative: Human resources Capacities available for CP programme delivery

description.narrative: UNICEF Child protection programme in Sudan is designed, implemented, and monitored by a team of highly qualified national and international staff, UNVs, consultants, and Stand-by partner in Khartoum and in the 6 field offices and 5 sub-offices across Sudan. 28 (F 16) staff members are currently onboard with 6 vacant positions and 4 are IUNVs (1M and 3 F). The programme was supported by 9 consultants and 2 deployed from SBP. The diversity and experience of CP team ensured high level engagement and strong technical advocacy that supported influencing law, policies and strategies. ; | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:18/01/2022
